System Role:
Act as an expert Full-Stack PHP Developer specializing in Modern PHP 8.x (OOP & MVC architecture), MySQL (via XAMPP/phpMyAdmin), and Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+).

Project Overview:
Build an "AI Facial Recognition Check-in System" with a robust Admin Back-office. The system includes mobile self-registration, a webcam-based check-in kiosk, and a comprehensive management dashboard for administrators. The code must be production-ready, highly organized using an MVC directory structure, and easy to maintain.

Directory Structure Requirement:
Organize the project cleanly:

/config (Database connection using PDO)

/models (Database logic and queries)

/controllers (Business logic)

/views (UI / HTML / PHP templates)

/api (Endpoints for frontend to fetch/post data as JSON)

/assets (CSS, JS, Images, face-api.js models)

1. Database & Security (MySQL on XAMPP):

Database Name: ai_checkin_db

Tables:

users: Store user info (id, name, student_id, face_descriptor [JSON], role [user/admin], status [pending/approved]).

check_ins: Store logs (id, user_id, session_id [1,2,3], scan_time, status).

Security:

Use PDO with Prepared Statements strictly to prevent SQL Injection.

Implement PHP Session-based Authentication ($_SESSION).

Only users with role: 'admin' can access files in the Admin Dashboard area.

2. Admin Back-office System:
Create a Sidebar-based Admin Layout containing:

A. Dashboard Overview (The Nerve Center):

Live Stats Cards: Total Users, Present Today, Active Session Status.

Visual Indicators: Real-time counter for each of the 3 sessions.

Session Status Timeline: Highlight the current active time slot (08:00-12:00, 13:00-16:00, 17:00-22:00).

B. Real-time Monitoring Board:

A "Live Stream" of check-in events. Use JavaScript (Fetch API / AJAX Polling or Server-Sent Events) to ping the /api/get_live_checkins.php endpoint so new scans pop up at the top without reloading the page.

C. User Management (Back-office):

User List: A table to view all registered users fetching data from the users model.

Approval System: Admin can toggle user status via AJAX.

Manual Check-in: Admin can manually insert a check-in record.

Search & Filter: Find users by ID or Name (implement using SQL LIKE).

D. Check-in Reports & Logs:

A detailed log history searchable by Date and Session.

Export Data: Generate a CSV file using PHP fputcsv() for attendance records.

3. Check-in Kiosk & Logic:

Webcam Interface: Implement face-api.js on the frontend (/views/kiosk.php) for real-time face scanning and descriptor extraction.

Business Logic (in Controller/API):

Compare the captured face descriptor with the JSON descriptors stored in the MySQL database.

Validate current server time (date('H:i')) against the 3 sessions.

Prevent duplicate scans in the same session using SQL constraints or pre-check queries.

Display UI feedback via JS SweetAlert or Toasts: "Scan Successful" or "Error: Already Scanned".

4. Tech Stack Details:

Backend: PHP 8.x (OOP/MVC).

Database: MySQL (MariaDB on XAMPP) using PDO.

Frontend UI: TailwindCSS (via CDN) + standard HTML5.

Icons: FontAwesome or Heroicons.

Charts: Chart.js (for the Dashboard Overview).

AI Face Recognition: face-api.js (Client-side processing).

Step-by-Step Instructions:

Provide the schema.sql file to create the database and tables in phpMyAdmin.

Write the config/database.php using PDO.

Build the MVC structure for User Management (Model, Controller, View with CRUD operations).

Develop the Live Overview board using JS Fetch API polling a PHP endpoint.

Create the Logic for the 3-session check-in and duplicate prevention.

Ensure all Admin pages check for $_SESSION['admin'] and redirect unauthorized users